Our high-quality paper fights ink bleed, which lets you use both sides of the page to maximize notetaking space. The Five Star app and our specially-designed paper make it easy to scan, study and organize your notes wherever you go! Use the app to create instant digital flashcards, track your study progress, and study anywhere, anytime. KEEP IT ALL TOGETHER Our pockets are tough enough to handle all your handouts and loose papers. Reinforced pockets help prevent tears and keep papers organized, giving you one less thing to stress about.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The Perfect Companion for Organized Note-Taking
reviews.reviewText: Oh, the Five Star Spiral Notebook, the behemoth of all notebooks that has become my trusted companion for organized note-taking. This colossal notebook with its impressive 5-subject capacity has proven to be a game-changer for my study sessions and work endeavors.Let's start with the size. This notebook is not for the faint-hearted, as it offers an abundance of space to jot down notes, ideas, and doodles to your heart's content. The large size allows me to keep all my subject notes neatly organized in one place, eliminating the need for multiple smaller notebooks. It's a true powerhouse of note-taking potential!The college-ruled paper is a dream come true for those of us who have a lot to say. The lines provide just the right amount of guidance without being too constricting. Each page is spacious enough to accommodate extensive note-taking, ensuring that no idea or detail gets left behind. The paper quality is top-notch, fighting ink bleed-through and providing a smooth writing experience.One of the standout features of this notebook is its water-resistant cover. Accidental spills or light rain showers are no match for its protective shield. This feature gives me peace of mind, knowing that my precious notes are safe and secure, even in unpredictable situations.The inclusion of the Study App is a delightful bonus. It seamlessly integrates with the notebook, allowing me to digitize my handwritten notes and access them on my preferred devices. This feature has revolutionized my study routine, as I can easily review and annotate my notes anytime, anywhere.Despite its larger size, this notebook remains durable and well-constructed. The spiral binding keeps the pages securely in place, and the plastic dividers help keep my different subjects organized. It's a reliable companion that withstands the rigors of daily use.In summary, the Five Star Spiral Notebook is a force to be reckoned with. Its substantial size, high-quality paper, water-resistant cover, and innovative Study App make it the ultimate choice for organized note-taking. Whether you're a student, professional, or simply someone who enjoys putting pen to paper, this notebook is a must-have for your arsenal.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Exactly as advertised!
reviews.reviewText: These are perfect, and offer more paper than others that are similarly or higher priced. The pockets are also great, helping me keep track of scrap papers that I want to transcribe into the notebooks at a later date.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent quality and long-lasting notebook
reviews.reviewText: Five Star has been a favorite since I was in high school several hundred years ago. This notebook doesn't disappoint. It has very good quality paper with clear and consistent lines.With regular pens, even gel point, there is no bleed-through at all. However, there is some bleed with Sharpies and similar markers. It is minimal but does happen.The perforations work pretty well but I sometimes have to crease the paper along the perforation first. Just to ensure a smooth tear out without ripping elsewhere. That is, unfortunately, normal with perforated sheets.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great journal for random ideas in multiple subjects
reviews.reviewText: The only reason I didn’t give it 5 stars is I think it’s a bit on the pricey side. However, the paper seems to be of decent quality and the pages are easy to tear out when needed. I also like the folders between the different subjects. I don’t use the app at all, because I like the old school journal feel. I use it for meal and exercise planning as well as a journal and a sketch book.
